First Paragraph:
There once was a baseball team named the Minnesota Twins. They were playing on a brisk fall day
against the Houston Astros. The score was 1 to 1 in the bottom of the 7th. The twins are up to bat 
with their star player, Buron Buxton. The bases are loaded with two outs. 

Middle:
The Twins won the match eventually. As new rising stars, they were praised and admired by numerous other teams and also the media. In the evening celebration after the match, their parents and friends collaboratively made a special gift for them. When they opened the large gift box, they were shocked and touched. 

End:
